      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>/wiaposts/relevance-of-guru/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5115-Relevance-Of-Guru.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Relevance Of Guru&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Relevance Of Guru 
    &lt;div id=&#34;relevance-of-guru&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#relevance-of-guru&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Without Questions in life what is the need for a Guru?  &lt;br&gt;
If my questions are well defined then do I need a Guru?  &lt;br&gt;
Guru helps in defining questions well  &lt;br&gt;
or answering whatever you ask?  &lt;br&gt;
Does he empower you by giving more information  &lt;br&gt;
or make you restless by holding half answer?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Who Is Guru</title>
      <link>/wiaposts/who-is-guru/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 30 Aug 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>/wiaposts/who-is-guru/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;/assets/images/wiapost/5029-Who-Is-Guru.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Who Is Guru&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Who Is Guru 
    &lt;div id=&#34;who-is-guru&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#who-is-guru&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We all know the Samskrut definition of Guru  &lt;br&gt;
The remover of darkness.  &lt;br&gt;
But whose darkness?  &lt;br&gt;
How does he remove?  &lt;br&gt;
What is this darkness about?  &lt;br&gt;
What is the meaning of remove?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Omkara Dharma tradition,  &lt;br&gt;
Knowledge &amp;amp; Wisdom has been so important  &lt;br&gt;
that from the time immemorial  &lt;br&gt;
Many people came forward.  &lt;br&gt;
At the time of leaving for the cause of Knowledge &amp;amp; Wisdom  &lt;br&gt;
Some of these people had comfortable life and some didn’t&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
